animal.description:
Bonnie-American Pit Bull Terrier/Boxer/Mastiff/Siberian Husky/mixed breed-female-spayed-10 months-Adoption fee: $250 plus tax. Update: Bonnie's fee has been partially sponsored by Dennis and Nadine and will be reduced to $50 plus tax. Meet Bonnie! This girl is best described as enthusiastic in everything she does.  Bonnie was surrendered to us because she was too much for her previous owner.  She was too strong and too energetic for her.  Bonnie knows some basic commands.  She is housetrained but crated or kenneled when left alone because she likes to chew.  She very seldom has accidents in the home when supervised.  Bonnie is good with other dogs  but too much for cats.  Bonnie can be jumpy and mouthy but with direction and adequate exercise she does better.  She loves to play with kongs, toys and play in the water.  She does need some work on leash pulling but Bonnie is very smart and should do well with a good leader and consistency.  Bonnie did well on her dog test here too.  She can be a bit much but she does everything with enthusiasm so if she has an owner that can channel her energy and teach her obedience, the skies the limit with her.  Bonnie would be best in a home with older kids.  If you are interested in meeting Bonnie, apply at www.cchswi.org  

I am fixed, current on my rabies, distemper and kennel cough vaccinations. I am heartworm negative(dogs 6 months and older are tested at CCHS) and started on heartworm prevention. I have been de-wormed and I have also been microchipped. I will also be inspected by 
 a vet and receive a Certificate of Veterinary Inspection.  If you are interested in me, please head to the CCHS website at www.cchswi.org and fill out an application. Thank you! DATCP License 266742-DS

animal.description: Hi, my name is Hendrix, I am approximately 5 months old I currently weigh 20lbs, once I am full grown, I should weigh about 40lbs. I am a super sweet and loving and may need a little extra time to adjust to my new home and surroundings. Once I am comfortable, you will see what a fun loving and energetic boy I am. Please understand that I am still a puppy that has a lot of energy and will need a home that is able to provide me with daily excersise, training and ongoing socialization. I would also benefit from force free training that will help me learn proper manners. I will need help with my house training, so please be patient with me, the staff have been working with me and I'm doing pretty good, but, I still need some guidiance. I should be fine in a home with children of all ages as long as we are monitored, but I would first love to meet them to ensure that we a good fit. When you are unable to supervise me, it is highly recommended by the staff that I am crate trained, this will help keep me safe. I know that when you meet me, you will fall in love with me, but please remember I am a life long commitment. I am patiently waiting for my furever home...Is it you? My adoption fee is $350 that helps with the cost of my care. Please also note that I am up to date on my age appropriate vaccinations and should meet my new veterinarian within 2 weeks of my adoption to ensure that I remain healthy and keep on a regular vaccination schedule. If your are interested in adopting me or another homeless pet at Macomb County Animal Control, please complete an application at the link below and an adoption counselor will be in contact with you. https://animalcontrol.macombgov.org/AnimalControl-AdoptionApplication

animal.description: Hello my name is Luna! I am a girl that is out of this world! I have alot of energy and love to run and learn! I have been to doggy playgroup and have a very rough playstyle. My ideal family would consist of very active adults only. I would make an excellent running partner! I need a family that is willing to work with me and devote time to ongoing training. I have been in foster with the shelter's Animal Enrichment Manager. I ended up with her because I displayed some behavior problems that needed more work than could be done in the shelter environment. Even though I am still young I would not be a good fit for a first time dog owner. I have a special adoption procedure because of my behavior quirks and will not be a first come, first served adoption. Please fill out an application if I would be a good fit for your family! Once we approve your application my foster mom will give you a call to talk about me. If this dog has been successful in our play groups it is not a guarantee that a dog will be social with other dogs in their home or in public settings. Dogs are individuals and have personality conflicts, just like us. Play groups do not guarantee that territorial or resource guarding issues will not surface in the home. While play groups do help us get to know the dog's better, once they are adopted their new environments and new relationships will influence their behavior in ways we cannot predict. The Adoption Fee Includes: - initial canine distemper combination vaccination - first worming or stool check - rabies vaccination (for animals over 3 months of age) - AVID microchipping - flea treatment/preventative - spaying or neutering Adoption fee: $175.00 Per state law, ALL ADOPTERS must purchase a non-refundable 2021 dog license at time of adoption for any canine three months and older. The cost of the license is $7.00. (Senior Citizen or Person with Disability-$5.00) All dog adoptions come with free leash and collar.

animal.description: Hi, my name is SHORTIE and I would love to meet you. I am a Neutered Male Staffordshire Bull Terrier and English Bulldog. The shelter staff think I am about 5 years old. I have been at the shelter since Jan 25, 2021. Meet Shortie! This little meatball came to the shelter as a stray, so shelter staff and volunteers are still getting to know him. Personality: Shortie is the sweetest boy you`ll ever meet! Despite his goofy self, he loves to sit on your lap and get lots of cuddles! His favorite trick is to sit and he is very treat motivated and would love to learn more tricks with you! History: Shortie has shown some reactivity and stiff-body language towards other dogs while at the shelter, so he would prefer to be your one-and-only fur baby (more cuddles for him)! Energy levels: He may be compact, but he is one energetic dude! Shortie is just a bundle of joy! He would love to go on short walks with you around the block and snuggle with you afterwards! Ideal home: This little man has a LOT to say, so he should not go home to apartment-style living (apt, duplex, condo, etc). Ideal family: Shortie is a silly guy, who is sure to make you laugh and keep you on your toes! Because he is a bit of a `wild child,` children in the home should be OLDER, to be able to understand his body language and stay standing when he throws his weight around. All the children in the household should be present for a meet and greet with this guy! Are you ready for this little snorter? Come down and meet him today!

animal.description: Meet Scout! Scout is looking for a home that is ready to do some work with him on his socialization. Scout is about 2.5 years old, fully vetted, and he weighs 72 pounds. Scout was in his previous home since he was 6 weeks old, but he was surrendered to us due to his behavioral and social issues. Scout seems to have some fear based reactions with women, children, and strangers and would really benefit from working with a trainer to get through those fears. His previous family told us that he does well with other dogs and he had not been around cats. Scout had been living with a young kid in the home for quite some time but the day after he was neutered he snapped at the kid and was brought to the shelter to keep the kid safe. Scout was described as a great dog prior to this incident though and we believe that in the right home that is willing to help him through this, he will be a wonderful companion! He is potty trained, knows basic commands, and he loves to ride in the car. Scout has been around sheep and goats and did well with them but he does seem to chase small animals like squirrels and rabbits. Scout loves to get outside and go for walks but he does tend to pull on the leash when he is excited and could use a little bit of leash training in his new home. He was described as friendly, playful, outgoing, high energy, and protective. If you would like to meet Scout give us a call to set up an appointment!

animal.description:
Calling all large breed lovers! Meet Sarah! This 1 1/2 yr old 95lb Cane Corso is ready to to find that perfect home! Sarah is a big girl with a big heart. She is friendly, playful, and oh so affectionate! Sarah doesn't understand how big she is sometimes, so older kids with prior dog experience, or a home without kids, would be best. She would also do best as the only dog in the house. It is unknown how she would do with cats.

Sarah has hip dysplasia in her right hip. This means that the ball of her femur does not sit in the socket of her hip joint. We have put her on joint supplements and pain medication to keep her comfortable. In the future, she may need a procedure to remove the head of her femur to prevent rubbing and pain (FHO - femoral head ostectomy). Keeping her slim, staying on arthritis and pain medication, and daily gentle exercise will keep her in the best shape until surgery is needed.

An experienced owner who can keep Sarah as comfortable and pain-free as possible is necessary. If this is you, please give us a call to learn more. Meets by appointment only. Call to schedule a meet. 518-885-4113.

animal.description:
Feeling a bit blue? A little lonely? Is it getting dark a bit too early? Bright can fix all of that - he's a beam of love and light in dog form! Bright came to CCR after his owners were unable to care for him anymore. He's a 7 1/2 year old Great Dane/pittie mix who tips the scales at 83 pounds. Despite his beefiness, Bright thinks he's a lap dog! He loves to snuggle and cuddle, and nothing makes him happier than some love time. Bright is your typical elephant-who-sees-a-mouse scaredy cat - he can be worried going for walks in new environments or when he hears big new sounds! Once he's comfortable, this guy LOVES to go for walks in the woods, sniff around under the snow, and then come home to a roaring fireside snooze! Bright is currently living in a foster home where is foster mama says he's just a doll! Because of his tough early life, Bright has some issues sharing his stuff with other dogs, so he'll need to be the only dog in the home. He does fine with dog-savvy cats - he's living with two now! We're looking for a low-key suburban or rural home where Bright can stretch his legs without the noise and stress of city living. He's a low-key, mellow adult guy who wants a low-key, mellow home where he can finally have the love and security he deserves. Bright isn't comfortable with young children.

To meet Bright, please submit an application at chicagocaninerescue.org!

animal.description: Darling Dutches here! I'd like to say at your service but really, it's you who should be serving me. You see, I'm a 2-year-old Pit Bull Terrier/Cane Corso mix who somehow ended up at The New Albany Floyd County Animal Shelter when my previous owner was moving and couldn't take me with them. I'm looking for some place to call my very own kingdom and I was hoping that you would come along and make my dreams come true! I'll repay you by letting you walk me, feed me, and tell me I'm pretty. I guess I'll also give you some kisses and cuddles but only if I deem you worthy. I've never met whatever a "cat" is but they sound like I may be too tempted to chase them. They tell me I'm already spayed, micro-chipped and up to date on vaccinations. animal.description:
Adoption Fee: $300
Adoption Application: www.wherethewildthingsarerescue.com

Gender: Female
Breed/s: Cane Corso
Approximate Age: 8 months
Approximate Weight/Size: Current 60 lbs / Giant (Future)
Good with: People and Large Dogs
Not Good with: Cats
Fully Vaccinated: Yes
Neutered/Spayed: Scheduled
Microchipped: Yes
House Trained: Almost
Crate/Kennel Trained: Yes
Important Notes: Sister to Maya and Lianna

Hi everyone! My name is Maya. I am a Cane Corso pup approximately 8 months old. Would you like to know my story? It doesn’t start out great like most rescues, but thankfully I know the best life is on its way. You see I am officially a part of WTWTA Rescue and they take loving rescue kids like me and my sisters pretty seriously.   

So, my journey began when my sisters and I were found along a country road dumped off by our previous owners. I know what your thinking, how could somebody abandon beautiful kids like us…sadly this happens more often then it should. My sisters and I decided to stick together while we were off fending for ourselves near the woods. cause that’s what sisters do.  We were better as a pack than separated from one another. Thankfully a Good Samaritan who knows mastiffs saw us and picked us up. They were diligent about where we would be placed and who they would allow to rescue us so we could be kept safe. We arebeyond grateful for that.  

You see being an italian mastiff breed, we are a pretty “BIG” deal!….see what I did there :P So they contacted WTWTA who knows kids like us well and are specialized in placing our breeds in the right home. Since being a part of WTWTA we are learning what it feels like to be loved. They took us to get vaccinated. I was nervous at first going to the vet’s, but quickly overcame that and did well. I received all the necessary vaccinations and tests.  

Let me tell you I have the most guardian spirit out of my sisters. So It will take me a minute to feel safe and not be on gaurd around humans. However, when I let you in I will give you all of me and sleep in your arms like a baby. When I went to get vaccinated, they arranged for a driver for me. I know what you’re thinking, a girl like me should have a chauffeur. Well, that’s what I thought too. On the way to the vet I was mesmerized by how fast everything was moving. I didn’t want to miss it. While riding, my driver introduced me to Broadway musical but I’ve decided I’m more of a country and Today’s hits kind of gal. What really made me like country was when my driver played ‘Forever Girl’ by Jon Langston. My favorite line was “she’s everything in my whole world, that’s my forever girl.” It gave me hope to know I will be someone’s forever girl someday soon.

After our adventurous drive they arranged for me to have a spa day! Talk about rolling out the red carpet. While in the tub I liked to play a game called “Can you keep me in here?” I won the first round but my stylist was the champ. Can you keep a secret between you and I? I’m actually happy my stylist won. To be treated with such care felt luxurious. I am a luxury kind of lady. Then shortly after I showed off my quick ability to snatch their food off the counter within seconds. They didn’t even know it was gone. I blamed it on my sister. Suckers!

I am still working on potty training and leash training, so you will have to be patient. I am still coming into who I am, and it may take me a while to completely open up and adjust. I am unsure about other dogs and would need some time and folks to go slow with introductions. So if you currently have another dog, we would need to do a meet up to ensure we like each other. I am not sure about small animals so no cats or smalls breeds. I would prefer a nice fenced in yard to play in since I am a giant breed I need room to run! If your wanting a pup with unconditional love then you came to the right place :) 

If you are interested in Maya please list her in your adoption application.

animal.description:
If you are interested in adopting Bridget, please email Sandy at cheneylewis@verizon.net.


Are you looking for a young dog that already knows the basics and has endless love to give? Who is smart, curious and playful? Who would be happy both on long rambling walks and as a couch potato sidekick? Meet Bridget -she is a love bug and never misses a chance for a cuddle. She is quiet, well-mannered, and loves affection. She is housebroken, and has stayed alone for up to four hours with no problem. Her foster mom reports that she has the run of the main floor and has been a lovely guest. She is a great eater, takes treats nicely, doesn't beg (too much), and sits patiently for the leash. She sleeps by herself (on a comfy chair) all night without any problem. And did we mention she is adorable?

Bridget is a strong and confident girl, but she can be fearful of new people (particularly adult males). She needs practice at learning to trust strangers and be less protective of her loved ones. Bridget has been practicing with good success on meeting guests outside at her foster's house (socially distanced of course) and has already made great strides in a short time. Bridget also needs some improvement in her lease manners -especially when she sees other dogs.
 
Because of Bridget's tentative nature around strangers and her strong protective instinct, she would do best in an adults only home. Bridget is waiting patiently to meet her forever humans!

animal.description:
Go go go go! That's my middle name! As you probably guessed from my breed, I am a wicked smart, high energy, fun and loving companion who is ready to wiggle my way into your heart! Wanna get moving and get more exercise? I'll make sure of that! Wanna cuddle buddy on the couch to keep you safe during scary movies? I'm down for that too! Whatever adventure you want to take, I'm your girl! Hikes in the woods, kayaking, long runs, hunting, fishing, let's go go go! 

Some facts that you may want to know about me...I am 40 lbs & the vet thinks I am "full grown". I am smart and know these commands & obey them "almost" all the time: sit, come, hold/wait, lay down, shake a paw/high five, inside, up, gentle. Oh & of course "TREAT"... my personal favorite. I am still working on: no jump, off, walk easy & stay. I am good in a crate and I would never think to potty in the house! 

I would do best in a home with a patient owner who understands my breed characteristics and wants to help me learn the manners that will help me be the best lady that I can be. An owner who understands that at just 9 months old, I am still very puppy! I am super smart and trainable, so don't think I'm a dummy....that's not ignorance showing, it's just my stubborn streak. I would love love an energetic doggie play friend who loves to play as much as I do! I love older/senior dogs too, but they don't love me so much. My energy and desire to play will probably drive them crazy. Got kids? Great, they can run and throw the ball with me! Got kitties? Well, I've never met one of those, so I don't really know if I like them or not. But, I am sure I'll like you! Just fill out an application at www.pawsitivetailskc.org, and come see if you like me too!

Crate/Kennel Trained: Yes
Important Notes: Sister to Luke

Hi I'm Lola, here’s a little backstory on me…

On December 30th 2020, WTWTA Rescue received a call from a local motel manager. They were informed that there were 2 pit puppies, my sister and I, abandoned outside of our room, left in our kennels, overnight on the coldest night of the year. Thankfully the motel employees put us back inside the room where we had been kept and began to adamantly contact WTWTA Rescue and called and called till they reached someone. When WTWTA came to check on our situation they realized we had not been fed or watered properly in days. The motel room was covered in our own feces because no one was taking us out to potty. We had to drink our own urine to try and get hydrated. Our mother had completely abandoned us and left us hungry and freezing to death. 

Thankfully, WTWTA Rescue immediately took us into their foster care program where we would be kept safe and warm until our quarantine period was up. While there we met a friend who went in quarantine with us. Her name is Marty you can read her story and bio on this website too. Let me tell you, those first couple nights we kept our foster mom hustlin with how much we ate and pottied. We are just so grateful to be alive! 

They think im about 4-5months old. Im the twin sister of Luke. Although my brother and I were left unable to fend for ourselves in the cold, we are survivors. We look at the brighter things life has to offer and you will notice that about me in my sparky and happy personality. Now, to the essentials…have you heard about this thing, I think you humans call it cuddling??…..Well I love it! It is one of my all-time favorite things to do. Affection is my favorite, I will shower you with kisses. Affection, makes me feel like I’m loved and cared for and like I’m worth all the good things life has to offer. I’m not as active as my brother but I do I enjoy practicing tricks. I like to show off how smart I am and I want my person to know I am here to listen to them. I am also considering opening my own business. Lola’s cuddle club will be the name. I’m hoping my cuddles will enhance other’s lives each and every day. If you pick me I will love you forever!

If you are interested in Lola please make a note in your adoption application

American Pit Bulls are a misunderstood breed; for this reason, we implore adopters to these beautiful dogs to be very vigilant in training and socialization. This breed is very energetic and will need daily exercise. Because of their strength and energy, apartment living may not be the best fit. This breed can be loving, loyal and very smart. 

The above behaviors and personality traits have been observed while at the Shelter. If this animal was relinquished, information is gathered from the owner regarding behavior. Our wonderful volunteers spend time with these animals and give input on behaviors and traits. However, this description may not be all inclusive to how this animal will act in a loving forever home. Introduction to established family pets should be slow and monitored always. The same goes for children and other family members. Adopting a pet is a big decision and should be thoughtful. We suggest researching different breeds to match traits and personalities to your lifestyle. When adopting a pet, please know that this pet will be with you for their lifetime; patience and consistency will make for a successful adoption. animal.description:
This handsome 80 pound Lab mix is called Teddy Bear ! This boy had a tough beginning in life and he endured abuse while living his life on a chain. This has not prevented this 3yr old Tennessee Lab mix from being a loving dog with people. He has been a happy dog for us to foster but we did find that that years on the chain has made him unfriendly with other dogs. This happens so often with chained dogs and is not their fault. You could not find a happier more people oriented dog than Teddy!! He enjoys car rides and hikes and walks very well on a leash. He is housebroken and loves his crate, and goes in on his own for a nap. Teddy does require a home with no other animals as he was never properly socialized while on the chain. Children over 10yrs old would be best due to his size. If you are interested in giving Teddy a dream come true happily ever after life, please email us at ccrtennessee@gmail.com
ADOPTION FEE REQUIRED. Contact ccrtennessee@gmail.com.

Hi I'm Drax,

So here I was in a shelter up in Orangeburg, SC with large painful masses of tumors on my body, heartworm positive and looking “pit”-iful and with no adopters willing to take me in to their family :(

I am approximately 2-3 years old American Bully. The shelter I was at originally was pleading for funds for a rescue to take me in….and nobody bit but guess who showed up on their front porch to come save me? You guessed it WTWTA. I must say they are some pretty rad people for us long shots .  

Once WTWTA took me into their pack my life changed in a way I didn’t think was possible. They didn’t waste time. They immediately made an appointment for surgery to help remove my painful tumors (non-cancerous) with one of the best surgeons in the area. Now their gone I’ve never felt better. What a weight off my shoulders….literally! Life is great! Now, I make people around me laugh with my grunt and snort sounds. They think I maybe 1/3 pig, 1/3 dog and 1/3 rhino …because the way I move reminds them of a big rhino.

When I want to be near you, I dig my front paws into the earth, bury my shoulders low to the ground, and truck to get to you like a happy rhino.  Although, I may be mixed with rhino, pit-bull, giant bearded dragons and who knows what else I’m a super chill and loving pup that’s as sweet as can be.

I am fully vaccinated and neutered. I am, however, heartworm positive. That doesn’t scare me though WTWTA knows how to take care of kiddos like me. I am great on a leash and will go where you lead me, unless I see something really fun or someone I love then Ill go excitingly in that direction like a baby rhino. Then I transform into a rhino hulk. I’m good with small dogs. If I’m being honest, I prefer humans over animals. I do not favor large alpha dogs. I like solid companions. 

So If you’re a laid-back lad or family that wants to chill and go on walks and snuggle on the couch I’m your guy.  

If you are interested in Drax please make a note in your adoption application via our website noted above.

animal.description: #579118Age: 3 years, 9 monthsWeight: 18 lbs How this pet arrived: This pet was brought in by their previous owner on December 9, 2020. Why this pet is the one for you:Are you looking for a pal with a personality as sweet as candy? Then you need to meet Jujubee! This little fellow is quite the cutie, and he's looking for an extra-special family willing to help him with his medical needs; Jujubee has a condition called Intervertebral Disk Disease (or IVDD for short) and has had some trouble using his back legs. Due to this ongoing disease, Jujubee is not a good candidate for a home with stairs, or a family looking for an active hiking/running partner. He has been improving wonderfully in our care, and his new family will need to speak with their veterinarian about a plan to keep him healthy and happy before adopting. In the past, Jujubee has gotten along well with respectful children, and with other small dogs; however, because of his condition, he'd rather watch the fun and games from the sidelines, rather than join in the action (if you're looking specifically for a playmate for another four-legged friend, Jujubee might not be the best match). So all that being said, do you think Jujubee might be the guy for you? If so, make an appointment to learn more today! animal.description:
Introducing this absolutely darling baby boy named Shaggy!!! This glorious mush and his littermates (all boys!) were named after scooby doo! These pups were born to a stray mama is a super poor, desolate area. Fortunately for them, an amazingly compassionate animal lover found them. She knew that where they lived their outcome would likely be poor, but she wanted to do everything she could to be a stepping stone to a life of greatness for each! She took them in and spoiled them with as much love as she could. She fed them not only dog food but she cooked for them and truly treated them as her babies! She snuggled and spoiled them and cherished every one of them, while simultaneously trying to create a plan for them to get a better life than where she was living would ever have to offer her. After several weeks of not finding a solution she felt great about, she reached out to us for help! Fortunately we had an amazing foster home available who was happy to help and be the next stepping stone to a great future! 
Once we got them they went straight to the vets! The vet gushed about what chunky adorable happy babies they were! And agreed on the thought that they were likely black lab/Australian cattle dog blends of some kind. No matter what they are, they are definitely AMAZING!!! So purely sweet!
In Shaggys foster home he is a master snuggler- and so super smart! He is the best of all worlds! Eager to please, eager to snuggle, eager to play, and so adorable with GLORIOUS ears!!! He is a chunky, brilliant character who is absolutely irresistible! He would love a home with another dog, but it is not required! He loves all kinds of play and exploration and is sure to grow to be such a Velcro dog! He will follow you everywhere and be your best friend for life! He is such a happy, positive spirit and needs parents who are just like that! Living a beautiful life, full of love, happiness and adventure! 
If this absolutely darling puppy is your dream come true, please visit our website and submit an application for adoption today!! www.greatdivideanimalrescue.org

animal.description:
Blueberry is such a GREAT dog. In all situations, she is just wonderful, truly, once she knows you (tentative at first). She is only about 4 to 5 years old and 55 lbs of kisses and mush, once she warms up. Someone really messed up her ears, trying to get her to look mean, but she is anything but that. Her beautiful blue color and gentle nature will melt your heart. Blueberry is fearful of men, but no aggression at all. She loves other dogs and we can cat test. She is truly just a big mush who will steal your heart for sure. If you like this breed, you will LOVE Blueberry. So pretty in person. CRPUPS@PTD.NET to contact us for any reason. (If you do not hear back from us within about 6 hours, send us your phone number, for there might be something wrong with your email! WE DO NOT TEXT) 
Lovable Mutts Adoption Center is a private, in home, all breed rescue/adoption facility, specializing in all ages and sizes of dogs.  We exist only on the kindness of your donations and adoptions!  We pride ourselves on being an HOLISTIC center and feed only holistic grain free foods and give daily, various, vitamins and supplements to all of our dogs. 

Our dogs are well socialized, very friendly, well mannered, affectionate, and in wonderful health. While some might be timid or shy, we work with our adopters in any way we can, to help them to work with their new family member. We give training tips and behavioral tips and even board for a very reasonable fee. Our dogs are extremely well cared for - most even know how to use a dog door by the time they leave us, know basic commands, and are crate trained!  We stand by our pups/dogs, and give 10 days for a refund and almost always take our dogs back at any age of their lives (can sometimes depend on the dog)! 

Lovable Mutts Adoption Center has an application screening process.  All applicants are asked to provide vet references, personal references, and a home visit.  We pride ourselves in matching up the right dog with the right home.  Sometimes this happens quickly and sometimes it might take awhile.  We hope you understand and are willing to wait for the perfect pup for your situation. We reserve the right to turn applicants down and to change our mind about a suitable match, for we are only concerned about what is best for our dogs.  Also note that we arrange our visiting hours around your schedule, as this is a private, in home facility.  We respond to all inquiries promptly, so if you have any trouble sending us an email, or have not heard back from us within 24 hours, please, CONTACT US AGAIN and check your spam!  (We all know how emails can be at times!)

Our dogs are spayed or neutered (if old enough), up to date on vaccines, wormed, heartworm tested, and free of fleas and ticks.  We temperament test our  dogs and they are all suitable for many family situations. Our dogs are well mannered,  and are in our family/home situation at this time (not kept in kennels or crates), and are worked with daily.  All of our dogs do well with other dogs and many do well with cats, and we can cat test. Adoption donations vary with age, breed, vetting, and training of the dog, and range from $250 to $500. This donation helps to pay for shots, de-wormings, spays, neuters, flea protection, heartworm/Lyme testing, treatments, and other vetting/issues that might be needed, for dogs in our care.  (We do not tend to place puppies or small dogs with kids under 6 and reserve the right to match who WE feel would be the best homes for our dogs.)  
Please, come adopt one of our Lovable Mutts - you will be so glad you did!

(IF YOU DO NOT GET A REPLY EMAIL WITHIN 24 HOURS, CHECK YOUR SPAM BOX - WE REPLY EVERY FEW HOURS TO EMAILS)

animal.description:
ALL adoptions require a completed application, vet check, home check and final contract.  The application to adopt can be found at www.camorescue.com.

stop scrolling you have found me Fletcher here does your son or hubby need another guy in the house I am their guy I love my bro’s, moms and sisters are okay but I am really about hanging with the bros. I have 3 legs lost it doing something I shouldn’t like crossing a road with out an adult won’t ever do that again I am lucky to be alive. I am 10 to 12 years old and weigh about 10 lbs I am house trained and crate trained I don’t like pads those are for sissies. I love to cuddle on the couch and watch TV and I must must always be with you don’t leave me alone that makes me very sad. Oh and yes I am a great guard dog I will alert you to every package being delivered before they are even on the door step if your interested apply at Camo Rescue 

Adoption fees are variable. Up to date vaccines, microchip, spay/neuter are included in the fee.

Once your application has been approved, we will put you in touch with the foster to set up a  meet and greet. We are a foster based RESCUE, not a shelter. All of our dogs are in individual foster homes. We conduct veterinary and personal reference checks during the application approval process. We select the best applicant for each dog, based on the dog's needs. 
For the safety of our small breed dogs and based on our past experiences, we will not place our dogs in homes with large breed dogs.    

CAMO rescue is a 501c3 whose primary focus is rescuing small dogs from the euthanasia list from high kill TX shelters.   
EIN # is 46-5486022
We rescue 800+ animals a year.

Follow us on Facebook at www.facebook.com/camorescue

Our donation link is http://www.paypalme/camorescue 

We are strictly volunteer based, no salaries are paid and 100% of donations go towards rescuing dogs.

animal.description:
Mojo is such a wonderful, sweet pup. He is 42 lbs and only about 9   months old. He is smart and does well in all situations. A fenced yard is important. Mojo is great with other dogs and cats and kids. Truly just a sweet pup in need of a forever home. Playful, smart, affectionate, and eager to please. So adorable in person and a must meet. (If you do not hear back from us within about 6 hours, send us your phone number, for there might be something wrong with your email! WE DO NOT TEXT) 
Lovable Mutts Adoption Center is a private, in home, all breed rescue/adoption facility, specializing in all ages and sizes of dogs.  We exist only on the kindness of your donations and adoptions!  We pride ourselves on being an HOLISTIC center and feed only holistic grain free foods and give daily, various, vitamins and supplements to all of our dogs. 

Our dogs are well socialized, very friendly, well mannered, affectionate, and in wonderful health. While some might be timid or shy, we work with our adopters in any way we can, to help them to work with their new family member. We give training tips and behavioral tips and even board for a very reasonable fee. Our dogs are extremely well cared for - most even know how to use a dog door by the time they leave us, know basic commands, and are crate trained!  We stand by our pups/dogs, and give 10 days for a refund and almost always take our dogs back at any age of their lives (can sometimes depend on the dog)! 

Lovable Mutts Adoption Center has an application screening process.  All applicants are asked to provide vet references, personal references, and a home visit.  We pride ourselves in matching up the right dog with the right home.  Sometimes this happens quickly and sometimes it might take awhile.  We hope you understand and are willing to wait for the perfect pup for your situation. We reserve the right to turn applicants down and to change our mind about a suitable match, for we are only concerned about what is best for our dogs.  Also note that we arrange our visiting hours around your schedule, as this is a private, in home facility.  We respond to all inquiries promptly, so if you have any trouble sending us an email, or have not heard back from us within 24 hours, please, CONTACT US AGAIN and check your spam!  (We all know how emails can be at times!)

Our dogs are spayed or neutered (if old enough), up to date on vaccines, wormed, heartworm tested, and free of fleas and ticks.  We temperament test our  dogs and they are all suitable for many family situations. Our dogs are well mannered,  and are in our family/home situation at this time (not kept in kennels or crates), and are worked with daily.  All of our dogs do well with other dogs and many do well with cats, and we can cat test. Adoption donations vary with age, breed, vetting, and training of the dog, and range from $250 to $500. This donation helps to pay for shots, de-wormings, spays, neuters, flea protection, heartworm/Lyme testing, treatments, and other vetting/issues that might be needed, for dogs in our care.  (We do not tend to place puppies or small dogs with kids under 6 and reserve the right to match who WE feel would be the best homes for our dogs.)  
Please, come adopt one of our Lovable Mutts - you will be so glad you did!

(IF YOU DO NOT GET A REPLY EMAIL WITHIN 24 HOURS, CHECK YOUR SPAM BOX - WE REPLY EVERY FEW HOURS TO EMAILS)

animal.description:
Shadow is such a sweet, gentle, laid back, timid dog. He is 6 years old and 65 lbs of wonderful, but it takes him some time to warm up. He was dumped at a shelter, after supposedly chasing neighbors goats. We find this hard to believe, for his hips are not great and he just does not move fast enough, nor have the energy it takes, to chase goats! Poor excuse made up, for a guy who no longer wanted to keep his dog. Shadow does well with dogs, and we can cat test. He is gentle and calm and a bit reserved and timid, til he knows you. He is so confused as to what he is doing here. Poor guy seems so beaten down and as if someone was a real jerk to him, most all of his life! Please, open your hearts and homes to this wonderful boy - you will be so glad you did! He is very handsome in person and a real gentle soul. CRPUPS@PTD.NET to contact us for any reason. animal.description:
This handsome boy's name is Frankie. He is a Blue Tick Coonhound and is believed to be around four years old. Frankie LOVES people and the outdoors to no end.
Frankie is one of our special medical cases as he was diagnosed with a strong heart murmur and needs medication for his condition. He is in very good spirits but will need to be seen by a veterinarian on a regular basis, and his exercise has to be monitored to prevent any further damage to his heart. His day-to-day life is pretty positive, and he doesn't act as if he has a heart condition, but potentially his life span can be cut short due to the severity of his murmur.
He does not seem reactive to other dogs but will need a mellow household due to his medical needs. Frankie seems to be fine being around cats, and we think he would be fine with children as well as long as they know not to rough house with him.
This sweet boy deserves all the love and care he receives and would make a great addition to any family who wants to make sure that this happy dog lives the remainder of his life in a good home.Please visit the following link on our website to learn about Second Chance's adoption process. http://www.2ndchanceanimalcenter.org/adoption.html

animal.description:
Hello, May name is Sis and I am only 7 months old. I was turned in by my 90 year old owner. He was worried I would get under his feet/walker and trip him. 

After bringing me to the shelter, the shelter veterinarian found that I have a continuous heart murmur that indicates I most likely have a congenital heart defect that is called a PDA or Patent Ductus Arteriosus. 

I am in need of a loving family that can take me in and have my heart evaluated by a veterinarian since the shelter does not have the equipment needed for this evaluation. 
I will need chest x-rays, an ECG and a Cardiac U/S to get a definitive diagnosis. I will also need to be evaluated by a surgeon for possible surgery or catherization procedure. 

Without treatment I will live for only a few years depending on the condition of my heart and the progression of disease found during the evaluation.

I am very sweet and cuddly and would love for a family to take me home and give me the best life I can have. Primary Color: Blonde Weight: 31lbs Age: 0yrs 7mths 1wks Animal has been Spayed

Meet Kasha! This sweet and energetic girl is ready to find her forever home. Kasha will be 3 years old in March and would love nothing more than to celebrate with her forever humans. She has never met a human she doesn't love, especially if they will play with her and give her belly rubs. Kasha did well at her vet visit and when she had a spa day at the groomer. She is such a social little butterfly! This girl would do best in home with older children, as her energy and excitement may knock little ones over. She does well with other dogs, but prefers to eat in her very own space as she becomes protective of her food. She loves romping and playing with her 4 foster fur-siblings, and would like to have a fur-sibling of her own in her forever home.

In typical border collie fashion, this girl is not only energetic, but she is also very smart! She walks well on a leash and knows basic commands of sit, down, off, and no. Although she is quick to learn, she is still working on her manners and will need ongoing support with this. She has been know to put her paws on the counter, but has learned this is not polite! She also loves to greet humans with a hug, she needs ongoing reminders that this is not polite nor welcomed by all humans she meets.

This young, active girl would love to find herself an active household. She would make a great jogging partner! Kasha requires a large fenced yard so she can show off her speed and her ball playing capabilities (chances are, her humans arm will become tired before she does!). She LOVES being outside, and needs a family who can spend lots of outdoor time with her.

Kasha is nearly 3 years old and weighs 45 pounds. She is house trained, crate trained and up to date with all vetting, including monthly preventatives. If you are interested in welcoming Kasha into your home, (and planning her upcoming birthday party!) please fill out an application.

Kasha is being fostered near Sedalia, MO.

Hi everyone! I am a very sweet girl looking for a calm, loving and patient family to call my own. I am shy at first but once I know you are an awesome human we are going to be the best of friends!

I would love daily walks and love.

If you are interested in meeting me, please go to www.ccrcdogs.com to fill out an application.

We do not have a facility for you to visit.

WE PROCESS APPLICANTS AND SET APPOINTMENTS BASED ON THE ORDER APPLICATIONS ARE RECEIVED

, so while you are welcome to email
ccrcdogs@ccrcdogs.com
with specific questions, you will want to complete the

ONLINE APPLICATION

ASAP

,

which can be found at www.ccrcdogs.com,

to secure your position in line for one of our dogs. You can also find

a description of our process on that same page. Puppies will not be available to be seen until their 10 day quarantine has passed. Our adoption fee is $200 for adults and $275 for puppies, which covers the cost of the spay/neuter, age appropriate shots and tests, medications to bring the dog to full health, and a free visit with one of our approved vets after adoption. The majority of dogs at CCRC are obtained from animal control centers, so there is often very little known about their history or even current habits. You can always expect to do some training, regardless of whether you adopt a dog or a puppy, including crate training, house training, and basic manners. CCRC provides a variety of materials and resources to assist you with this, as well as telephone support.

animal.description:
Jack is a very handsome Australian cattle dog/ Border collie mix around a year old. He is a very active boy so will need a fenced yard or acreage/farm type home where he can run and get exercise. Jack is good with other dogs but wants to play with them a lot so another dog that is too old or too small to tell him enough will not be a good fit. Dogs with his energy level he loves. Our foster home is working with him on some manners because like most herding breeds he likes to use his mouth to tell you hello and play. No one trained him when he was younger so an active home that will put time in him will be best. Jack is a love bug and will cuddle and give you lots of love. His coat is so soft he is a joy to snuggle with. He has been around kids and does good but when he gets running around and excited he will probably knock over small children. He is learning commands fast in his foster home. Jack would make a good sports dog he is smart and learns quickly.
To help pay for vet bills and care (transportation, food, toys, etc..) a $250 donation is requested at the time of adoption. All of our adoptions are contingent upon an approved application, home visit, reference check, obedience training agreement, and signing of adoption contract. All our dogs are spayed/neutered, vaccinated, and microchipped before adoption. Our dogs are companion animals that live indoors as part of your family. Please do not apply if your plan is to have them as outside dogs, garage dogs, porch dogs or outside kennel dogs. We do not ship dogs.
All of our dogs are in private foster homes. We are not a shelter with hours. A visit can be arranaged after an adoption questionnaire has been filled out and sent in. Please try email first. We are all volunteers that work so we can not easily take or make phone calls. 2/1/21 8:03 PM

animal.description:
Queso was brought to us as a stray. He is microchipped, and we contacted the owner registered on his chip. The previous owner had rehomed Queso to someone else. They contacted the person they rehomed Queso to, but they never called us or came for him. The previous owner said they had also gotten Queso from someone else and that he had been rehomed a few times. The owner registered on the chip advised he had to rehome Queso because he did not have enough time to spend with him or enough space for Queso to get proper exercise, and Queso tended to chew things/get destructive when left alone for long periods of time. Queso’s previous owner said that he does listen well and that he knows basic commands such as “sit” & “stay”. Queso loves water and playing fetch. He also loves to snuggle. Queso’s owner also said that he is housetrained.

Queso has proven to be a very playful boy, and he is always happy to meet other dogs here at the shelter. When meeting new dogs, Queso approached them with his tail wagging and exchanged sniffs and immediately wanted to play. Queso is high energy and his playful approach may be a bit much for more timid dogs, but he was happy to play with anyone who was willing.

When walking through our cat room, a cat in a kennel growled at Queso, and Queso barked at it. He stared at the cat for a few more moments and then continued sniffing around the room.

animal.description:
Sista is a Boxer/American Bulldog mix around 4 years old and about 70 pounds. 
Sista was found dumped along with her brother Bubba at 6 months old at someone’s home. Although a kind samaritan began looking for rescue, years passed and nothing came of it. This left Sista and Bubba to stay outdoors at their home on tethers, then in kennels. 
Sista is a sweet girl, that loves human touch and loves to cuddle. Sista came to us unsocialized with other dogs, but she’s starting to become very responsive to the slow introductions with other dogs. 
Sista is high heartworm positive and undergoing treatment which is covered by the rescue. Sista deserves a home like any dog does.
Be her light!

*Take Paws Rescue saves dogs from high-kill shelters in Southeast Louisiana, owner surrenders, and discarded dogs with uncertain futures. All of our puppies live in foster homes where they are socialized, and well cared for. An application will be required to make sure it’s the perfect match!

 If you are interested in meeting and/or adopting, the first step is to please visit our website to complete an application and read all of our FAQs: https://www.takepawsrescue.org/adopt 

**An inquiry/question on Petfinder is NOT an application. All known details about our animals are posted on their profile and updated daily. Other info would be discussed in detail with the foster during the application review process. Due to the number of inquires received (hundreds daily) we ask you submit an application on our website (a single application can be used for any dog with Take Paws Rescue).

The adoption fee for adult dogs covers age appropriate vaccinations, microchip, spay/neuter if not yet performed, heartworm test & appropriate heartworm treatment by the rescue's vet. All dogs in our care are also kept up-to-date on HW/Flea Prevention. Please see our website for more information. 

2021 Adoption Fee Scale for non-benefactor animals:
Puppies under 12 months - $300
Dogs over 12 months - $200

For additional information, including the adoption process and our adoption fee scale for all our adoptable pets, see our FAQs page: https://www.takepawsrescue.org/faq

*Any breed labels used by Take Paws Rescue, its employees/volunteers, or on vet records provided cannot be guaranteed.  Breed labels are given based on information obtained during intake and/or best guesses based on appearance and/or temperament of the dogs and Take Paws Rescue gives no assurance to the accuracy of these labels. Labels are necessary for postings to many animal networking sites, such as Pet Finder, and are no way a guarantee. Additionally, exact age and potential size cannot be guaranteed.

Husky experienced homes**
Niko is a 3 year old 42 lb long haired husky who was surrendered due to being an incompatible pet /placed in the wrong home. He was only in his last home for a few months before he became too much to handle. He is high energy, high drive, playful, curious, smart, mouthy, affectionate,  and has a tendency to push limits as he is used to getting away with everything. He will need an experienced home that can handle an outlet for both his energy and brain. He did live with a child in his last home  . He will not be placed with cats. His owner reported he can be dominant and territorial around new dogs at the dog park, but tends to warm up. He  has never lived with other dogs and can come off as aggressive initially.  He has some negative behaviors due to being bored, such as counter surfing, and acting on his shoe fetish. He only knows one command- sit-and will do it only when it's convenient for him. In the right home with structure and time, he will shine as an excellent companion.   He will come fixed, chipped, vaccinated, and heartworm tested negative.

animal.description:
**Please read Red's entire profile, which includes a link to the adoption application. Thank you!** 

Meet Red, a 14 month old, 45-pound, Australian Cattle Dog/Australian Shepherd mix young fellow.

Red is looking for an experienced owner(s) with a lot of patience to give him room to grow and slowly learn to trust people. He is a high energy pup who loves to run and play - chasing a tossed ball or playing tug are favorites.

He really likes rope toys, nylabones, and heavy duty stuffed toys he can happily chew on. He loves to go for walks, is great on a leash, and enjoys car rides, too A fenced yard is a plus for him.

A very smart boy, Red knows sit and stay, and is working on drop it, leave it, go to spot, and down. He is housebroken and uses his crate for sleeping at night and periods of time during the day.

Red must have some trauma in his past because he is very head shy. He does not like to be pet on his head, and getting his collar on and off is a bit of a challenge. But he is working on it. He also reacts to people and dogs while on the leash, but once he has had a chance to appropriately sniff he does settle down.

Red is not a match for first time dog owners. He also should go to a home with kids or cats - too much sudden movement. Another confident, well-socialized dog in his home could benefit Red.

If you are an experienced owner with lots of love and patience to give a dog like Red then you will be rewarded by watching him blossom, love, trust, and really enjoy life with you!

All dogs are up to date on vaccinations and spayed/neutered at the time of adoption.  All dogs require professional training to become the best family member they can be.

To adopt or learn more about Red, you must fill out an adoption application. To find the application, copy and paste this URL into your browser: WWW.GDRNE.COM/ADOPTION-APPLICATION [Adoption Fee: $495]  **  PLEASE READ: If a dog is listed, then s/he is currently available for adoption. Their information is correct to the best of our abilities and the information we have been given as of the day of posting. Please note, GDRNE does not guarantee the breed of any dog or puppy unless stated that we have run DNA. All breeds listed are educated estimates. Our dogs are rescued from various situations. It is most likely that both their parents were strays and even if not, mixes of some sort and that their grandparents were mixes as well. The dog may have some genetic material of an American Staffordshire Terrier (pit bull). The dogs are usually mixes of many breeds, making them a breed all their own - a True and adorable American MUTT. If you are interested in this dog, you must submit an application. Great Dog is not a shelter so there is no building you can visit. Our dogs live in private foster homes until adopted. To learn more about our *shelterless* rescue, adoption fees, and procedures, review the list of Frequently Asked Questions on our website at WWW.GDRNE.COM.

Buster arrived to us on January 7th, 2021, found out and about by a citizen. Buster is a very big boy weighing a whopping 75 pounds! This big boy is around a year and a half years old with an estimated birthday of 06/07/2019. Buster is a bundle of fun wrapped up in a gorgeous package. His striking brown eyes and impressive physique turn heads where ever he goes. Then comes the huge, adorably goofy, tongue out grin, and you're hooked! Buster enjoys toys and plays with them the same way he takes treats...gently. At the top of Buster's favorite things list is soaking up all the love he can get. His reaction to other dogs has been mixed, and he's pretty sure cats are useless, so this hunk of love will likely thrive in a home as your only fur baby. Buster's enthusiasm is infectious, and the family lucky enough to call him their own will reap the rewards of a lifetime of smiles.   

Our adoption fees vary, Shelter Dogs are $150, Prison Dogs are $200, Puppies are $250, and Popular Pure-Breeds are $400. The price includes: a Home Again Microchip, set of shots, de-worming, heartworm testing (if old enough), spay or neuter, and a 1 year rabies shot (if old enough). All dogs adopted must leave with a county license at an additional cost of $17, this fee is cash only. Adoption fees can be done using credit card or cash.  If you are interested in this dog, please call the shelter at 614-879-8368 or fill out an online application at www.hsmcohio.org

From owners:
“We are between a rock and a hard place with our dog. She’s an outdoor farm dog and we are renting our house. We’re technically not even supposed to have her at the property. With it being a rental my husband doesn’t want to put in “real” fencing and she gets out of everything we’ve tried. She’s a sweet girl but is quite the good guard dog and thinks both our house and our next door neighbor’s (who is a good friend) are her domain. My neighbor thinks she was about to bite her yard guy today. Hard to say if that’s true but it really scared her and my hubs is done.

She is mostly lab with some Dalmatian and maybe something else mixed in. She’s 5 1/2 years old and fixed, around 40-50lbs. Very good with kids. A bit excited sometimes but never rough. She’s been around (her son) since he was born. She stayed next door with my neighbor’s dogs for several months. But then the three big dogs (including mine) ganged up on the little dog so that was very bad. Not sure if it was a pack mentality thing or if the little dog just pushed her buttons. We also had chickens and she chased them some but never ate any. She is really sweet and gentle but maybe needs more room to roam? If you know of anyone who lives a bit more out in the country or at least has a fenced yard and would love an amazing dog.”

Meet Kiki and Violet. This adorable pair was rescued after their owner passed away. They lived on their own outside the previous owner's home before someone realized they needed help.

We would love them to be adopted together as they do love and depend on each other. They are lovely little girls who are easy-going and calm in the home.

Kiki is a love bug and likes to sit on your lap. Every once in a while she will feel a bout of playfulness and pull out a toy. She has a mild heart murmur that has been checked out by a cardiologist and it does not require medical treatment at this time.

Violet is a sweetheart who loves her people. She is gentle and kind.

Both girls need to be reminded to go potty outside.

We would love to see this pair live our their golden years being loved and well cared for.

They are updated on all shots and are chipped. Their combined adoption fee is $395.

We cover the medical to prepare the pet for adoption and the adopt donations go directly to cover those costs and range from $295-$495. Thank you for stepping up to save a life!

To expedite to meet with this dog, please go to our site at www.savinggreatanimals.org and fill out an application. We look at the first applications to arrive, so we hope to hear from you soon!

BAYO- Bayo is a wonderful male red heeler mix. This young guy is full of spunk! Bayo can be a little shy towards people upon first meeting them, but he loves to give love! If you have further questions regarding Bayo, send us an email or give us a call! 

Lewisburg Animal Shelter
300 Woodside
Lewisburg TN 37091
931-359-5948 Adoptions/rescue inquiries
931-359-7215 Strays/welfare checks/nuisance dog calls for ACOs
shelter.manager@lewisburgtn.gov

Follow us on facebook under Lewisburg Animal Shelter Volunteers to see more candid photos of the dogs in our photo Albums. The current adoption fee is $75 which includes the dogs spay or neuter and Rabies vaccination at a local vet, and covers the distemper/parvo vaccine and bordetella vaccine and dewormings it receives here at our shelter. No dog will leave the shelter to an adopter without being vetted first. 

By TN state law stray dogs are held for 3 days so they can be found by their owners before being put up for adoption or rescue. A dog found as a stray wearing a collar is held for 5 days before it is put up for adoption or rescue. Our shelter is a first come first adopt/rescue facility.There are no holds placed on dogs for potential adopters/rescue, however if a party is interested in a particular dog before it becomes available they may send an inquiry to shelter.manager@lewisburgtn.gov and those inquiries will be kept track of in order of received once dog becomes available. Adopters/rescues will be notified what order they are in in regards to each dog. They are available at 8am on the day they are available. Non vetted dogs will have an appointment scheduled and will be available for pickup for adoption the day after their surgery. Approved rescues may pull a dog and have vetted at their own expense once available to the public.

animal.description:
Mya is a candidate for our Foster To Adopt Program! She is currently undergoing heartworm treatment which will need to continue at Companions Animal Hospital in St. Cloud, MN.

Mya is lovable, loyal and well-mannered but trauma from her past made her intimidated by confident dogs. We placed Mya in a 2-week board & train program with K9 Off-Leash Training to help her gain confidence and learn basic manners. She has greatly improved and we are so excited for what the future holds for Mya! Adopters will receive a free training session with K9 Off-Leash Training to ensure Mya continues to keep up the great work!

Mya is a very sweet girl that absolutely loves people. She's extremely loyal to her family. She has stolen the hearts of many who have met her.

Mya is an active girl and will need a family that will bring her for daily walks or runs. She would also benefit from enrichment toys such as Kong balls or puzzle feeders.

Age: 7 y/o

Breed: Pitty Mix

Weight: 40 lbs

Kid-friendly: Yes!

Dogs: Yes! She has lived with other dogs and has done well but there has been incidents when a toy is involved. We suggest the dogs we separated during playtime and mealtime. Also, no free-standing toys or bones in the house.

Cats: Unknown but she was able to meet the office cats through their condo and had zero reaction. She was interested in the new friend but not overly interested where we were concerned. We do not recommend dogs be left alone with cats.

Crate trained: Yes! We recommend she eat and enjoy any toys or bones in her crate.

Potty trained: Yes!

Likes: Her people, relaxing, playing with other dogs and lots of love!

Health concerns: Heartworm Positive but currently undergoing treatment.

Behaviors: She struggles with resource guarding.

Adoption fee: $275

If you are interested in fostering, you must fill out a Foster Application here: http://www.greyfacerescue.org/foster

$50 discount for seniors (65+) and veterans. Adoption fees help pay for the dog's veterinary exam, vaccinations (rabies, distemper, and bordetella), HW test, blood panel, a microchip, and spay/neuter if needed and additional health needs specific to each animal.

animal.description:
Mitzi Ann is a beautiful German Shepherd senior girl that has been through so much in her life that we just want to cry at the circumstances she is facing once again. Over a year ago we came to know of Mitzi Ann and her plight which included being handed off to some different owners and her owner trying to turn her in to a shelter Because they were moving to a place with no fenced yard. The shelter was full and couldn't accept her but just weeks later she was found running loose and in danger Of being hit by a car. She was thin and really not in good shape at all. The shelter picked her up and Critter Cavalry Rescue took her in to help get her healthy and to Get her a wonderful new home. We finally found the best "only dog" home for her and we were ecstatic at the love and care she was going to receive. Now ..COVID Has hit and this beautiful soul is losing her home because he dad has lost his job and cannot find work and will be returning to his native Jamaica in February. Mitzi Ann Has blossomed into a stunning girl that plays ball every morning with her dad and stays so close to him as his companion in life. . She is about 85 pound now and her shiny coat and clear eyes just tells us that she has been well loved and cared for. She is thriving just as we prayed she would. she is housebroken, good on a leash and a perfect companion. She would prefer to be the only dog but has accepted a pair of puppies that recently joined the household and they too will be needing new homes. The adoptive couple are in tears to lose their dogs. Please give this 9 year old girl a chance to live out another 5+ wonderful years with you. She is a treasure. If you interested please email us ASAP. ccrtennessee@gmail.com

ADOPTION FEE REQUIRED. Contact ccrtennessee@gmail.com.

animal.description: Oh, hello. My name is Snowflake. I am so happy to be at the shelter!  My owner signed me over to the deputies after I was picked up. He just couldn’t care for me and I was in need of some medical attention.  The deputies took me to the vet where I had emergency surgery for infection. I am still in the recovery process, but I feel sooooo much better!  While I have been here the shelter took care of my vaccinations, they tested me for heartworms and I was negative, they gave me a microchip, and they had me spayed.  No more babies for me!!  The volunteers say that I am a sweet, shy girl that just wants love.  Is that the kind of dog you are hoping to find as a companion? Well my name is Snowflake and I am waiting for you!  FYI…the volunteers say that I take care of my “business” as soon as I walk outside! Good to know, right?

animal.description:
**Lou is currently awaiting extensive dental work**

MY STORY: Lou came to CBHS from a partnering animal rescue organization. Upon arrival at Cedar Bend, we discovered that Lou has no teeth and very tender gums. She eats wet food and still enjoys playing with softer chew toys!

AGE: Approximately 6 years.

TRICKS & COMMANDS: Sit

ABOUT LOU: Lou is a super calm and sweet lady who loves people! She walks like a proper little lady on a leash (you'll adore her prance!) and loves being close to her handler.

She loves chasing a tennis ball around outside, and she will sit pretty for any treats you'll give her. Lou loves to show you how fast she can wag her tail when she gets excited!

While Lou needs to be the only pet in the home, she's sure to give you all the love you could ever need from your new furry best friend.

Adoption fee includes spay/neuter, vaccinations, worming, microchip, and a start on flea/tick prevention.

For more information, please call CBHS adoptions at 319-232-6887 or email at adoptioncounselor@yahoo.com.

Sadie (also response well to Tater) is a 4 year old mutt mix looking for her forever home. She's a very active girl who cares deeply about her fitness and likes to stay consistent in her workout routine. Sadie has had a chaotic first four years of her life and now finds extreme comfort in structure and routines.  Especially if those routines include a mid-day cuddle session and reading a nice book before you tuck her into bed. 

Sadie is dog selective and would like to be in a home by herself with humans who will take the time introducing her to other dogs and be able to read the signs when she is just not that into it. Once she makes a friend though, they'll be besties for life. As you can see in her pictures she has a great pack of dog friends she loves to play with! Her foster has dedicated lots of time to her introductions to these dogs so that they can all be best friends! 

Sadie is house trained, crate trained, leash trained, and comes when called. She's just looking for a best friend to workout with and spend A LOT of her free time cuddling with. 

Please get in touch with her foster Darby by email darby.knoll44@gmail.com to learn more about Sadie and the possibility of meeting her!

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.
Name:Isaiah
DOB:1/20/2017
Weight:20
Adoption Fee: $375

Hi, my name is Isaiah, but my foster family calls me Izzy!

I came from a shelter in Oklahoma and I was really really scared when I arrived at my foster home. If anyone so much as looked at me or walked in my direction, I ran straight to the back of my crate and hid.

After a few days of quiet time in my own space, I have really opened up to my foster mom. She was patient enough to let me approach her on my own terms, so I'll need to find a forever family that understands and does the same. I promise your patience will pay off and I will be hopping on your lap and making myself comfortable in no time!

Because I am easily frightened, I'd like to go to a quieter home with no young children--they're a bit too unpredictable for me. I'm also a bit jumpy and mouthy when I get excited. My foster family has been correcting my behavior, and says I'm making lots of progress already!

There are two big dogs and one cat in my foster home, and while I wouldn't mind a buddy to play with, I'd prefer a buddy of the canine variety. I don't think I've had much exposure to cats before, so I will chase and bark at them. I'm also perfectly happy as an only dog, although having another dog around might help me build my confidence.

I am very treat-motivated, so I can certainly be bribed to become your new best friend. I also love to chew on bones and chew toys. I sleep in my crate in my own room at night but you'll have to bribe me with treats to get me in the crate. Can you blame me? Once I trust you, I just want to be with you all the time! I only sleep in my crate because my current foster brother gets snappy when he's sleepy. Otherwise, I'd be trusted with free roam of the house (so long as I get enough potty breaks). I'm working really hard on potty training and think I'd continue to benefit from a regular routine/schedule.

If you think we might be a good fit, please fill out an adoption application--I'd love to tell you more about myself and get to know you, too!

An adoption application is the best way to show your interest in an animal. Please check out our website, www.ruffstartrescue.org for more details and additional pictures on any of our animals! All Ruff Start dogs and cats are spayed/neutered, up to date on age appropriate vaccines, microchipped, dewormed, and on monthly flea/tick and heartworm prevention (dogs) as well as heartworm tested (dogs). Ruff Start Rescue is a foster based rescue. Animals are located in homes throughout Minnesota. We do not have a facility where animals are kept. Ruff Start Rescue Adoption Policies: http://www.ruffstartrescue.org/info/display?PageID=11744

Gordo was rescued out of Stanislaus shelter. He, his mom Delillah and his brother Bam Bam. They had issues with them together in the kennel so were rescue only. Once seperated from each other though they have became great dogs. Gordo has not been in a foster home yet but currently shares a kennel at our facility with 2 other dogs and does great. he's been very sweet with us and has tons of energy. Delillah and Bam Bam are in a foster home so have worked on potty training and crate training and are doing great. These dogs cannot be adopted together as they do much better seperated, as they tend to feed off of each other.

**NO SMALL CHILDREN

***MUST HAVE BREED EXPERIENCE

**NO OUT OF STATE ADOPTIONS

****PLEASE DO NOT CALL TO CHECK STATUS OF A DOG...PHONE CALLS ARE FOR EMERGENCIES ONLY. EMAIL US WITH ANY QUESTIONS ON ADOPTION AS WE DO NOT GET BACK TO PHONE CALLS ABOUT ADOPTION.

Shots up to date (DHPP), wormed, micro chipped, altered (spayed/neutered). We also now give one free vet visit with our local vet within first 3 days of adoption!!

Adoption cost for this dog is $250

We are a rescue, and although we have a facility in Modesto most of our dogs/pups are currently being fostered in or around our area. So please be willing to make the trip to see them if you are from out of the area. Our adoption process REQUIRES that an application must first be submitted and approved prior to meeting any of our pets. Just note that we may get several responses on one pet at a time so just because you have an approved application does not mean said pet is on hold for you. One must FIRST confirm an appointment to meet the pet after an approved application has been sent. To inquire about this specific pet, please write to info@pupznpalz.org for an application. Please remember to put the pets name in the subject line when emailing, and on the top on the application. It helps us to help you that must faster. We are a group of volunteers, and ask that you please bare with us. We will get to each person just as quickly as we can. If you do not hear back from us within 24 hours, please send another request as we have been having problems with e-mail.

email: info@pupznpalz.org and ask for an application for which dog you are interested in

phone: 209-480-8662 (9-6 pm only please, cell phone, emergencies only please...do not call to ask status of dog, email please)

**ADOPTION EVENTS: typically every Sat at Modesto Petco 2021 Evergreen Ave from 12-3

**OUR FACILITY: Located at 1430 Carpenter Lane Suite B (by appointment only as we do not have set hours)

animal.description:
Astrid is a petite husky mix who is approximately 7 years young. She was found as a stray, so her previous life is a complete mystery. She currently weighs about 40 lbs and may gain a little more weight but should stay well under 50 lbs. She was found with a skin condition that may have led to some fur loss - it is possible that she may become a little more fluffy as she continues to eat enough good quality food.

Astrid loves being part of a family. She loves her foster family's boys, especially the 8 year old boy, and happily walks with him on a leash and will even trot beside him in a pseudo jog if encouraged. When allowed, she happily sleeps on the couch next to her human - any human will do - she shows love to everyone she meets!

Astrid has happy feet. She uses her front paws to express a variety of emotions - if she's happy to see you, impatience with the speed at which you are feeding her, and several other, as yet, undeciphered dances. They are one of the most unique things about her character!

The most unique thing about her appearance is her bi-colored eyes. Many dogs have two colors, but Astrid's darker eye is a beautiful shade of amber that is very unusual in a dog.

All that perfection does have a few points that need to be taken note of. Astrid needs to be the only dog in her household. She's a resource hog and can't be trusted to share space around other dogs for eating, watching humans eat, playing with toys (even though she doesn't really play with toys), or even sharing the same doorway out to the deck. She does ok in an outdoor setting with other dogs, and the shelter reported that she "got along with everything", but in the household setting, that has not proven to be the case. She does not have this resource guarding issue with humans - it is possible to pet her while she is eating, and you can certainly walk out the door when she is on the other side of it. She also needs work on her housetraining. While she came into her foster home obviously familiar with being in a home, her skills need to be adjusted.

Astrid sleeps quietly in a crate all night and enjoys spending time outside during the day. She is not a barker or a digger and seems to enjoy watching the neighborhood activity. She is not overactive - her morning walk seems to satisfy her daily exercise needs.

Astrid is a wonderful dog and would do well in either a family or without children. She's confident, doesn't mind the vacuum cleaner, and doesn't bark in her kennel. In return for your patience with her few issues, she will give you love, loyalty, and laughterAdoption fee includes spay/neuter, microchip and rabies and other core vaccinations.

animal.description:
Hello! My name is Athena. I've been told I am quite a beautiful little lady. They aren't wrong! I'll take the compliment, thank you!

I am a sweet and friendly girl who has so much love to give! I absolutely adore my humans and enjoy snuggling with them. Spending a nice evening snuggled up to my favorite person sounds just about perfect to me! Speaking of my people, my foster family includes a couple small humans and I think they are pretty great. I can get a bit bouncy so I would need to be shown how to be calm when around tiny humans if my new home had them. I mean them no harm I just get happy to see them! Though I tend to be more on the easy going and calm side I do have a silly side that I let out every now and then. I enjoy playing with my canine foster siblings and my toys. We have quite a bit of fun together. 

Great news! My foster family says that I am a very good girl and know to do my business outside. When going for a walk I am well behaved and don't usually pull. I will even potty on leash too. My foster family has been working with me and teaching me all the things. I know sit, down and come so far. I would be happy to learn anything you might want to teach me as long as it comes with yummy treats! While my foster family is away I spend time in my crate. Though I would rather be wherever they are I don't mind waiting patiently for them to come back. 

If you are looking for a happy, sweet, cuddly, playful girl then you found me! I can't wait to meet you soon! 



--------------------------------------------


All our Warrior Dogs will have all age appropriate medical care and vaccines, a microchip, and spay/neuter before adoption unless age is a factor with a puppy younger than 6-12 months at the time of adoption. If that is the case, the spay/neuter will be covered in the adoption fee and the owner will be responsible to have the procedure completed at a Warrior Dog Rescue Veterinarian at the appropriate time.

Please note that the majority of our dogs in rescue are from shelters where they have been found as strays or abandoned. Their breed description is based on our very best educated guess based on physical characteristics and their dispositions. If they came to our rescue as an owner surrender, the breed description will be listed as provided by the previous owner.

Adoption Fee - $450

To apply for this pup, please submit an Adoption Application at http://warriordogrescue.com/adopt/adoption-application/

animal.description:
Meet our sweet girl Princess! She is a 2 year old Pit mix that came to us from a partner shelter in Georgia in November 2020. Princess can be very shy at first, but once she warms up to you, she'll be your loyal companion. She walks pretty well on a leash but can be easily startled by loud noises or fast cars going by. She is very very treat motivated and just wants belly rubs all the time! After some playtime, she would love a cozy dog bed to curl up on or a big couch for snuggles. She is very loyal and loving, making her the perfect companion! Since Princess can be easily overwhelmed with new situations and tends to be very attached to "her person", she would prefer to be in a home with very little foot traffic and also a home with a single owner. Princess is also dog friendly, and we believe that her confidence would come out more if she were to live with another dog. She can be a bit too much energy for some dogs, so she would need to meet another dog prior to adoption. If you are looking for a big lovebug, and someone to just absolutely spoil with attention, then Princess is your girl! 

If you think that Princess could be a good fit for you, please submit an online application. A generous donor has sponsored Princess's adoption fee! That means she will go home for $0 with an approved adoption.
